In fact, the aim is to reassure investors against business on the Asian financial markets, which are in the first time zone, where a decision by the Congress could influence the business on Monday.
So far, however, it is not quite clear when the two chambers of the American Congress will vote on the law, and there is also a lack of clarity as to whether the last minute negotiations could not fail in a problem.
