According to statistics, between 30-75% of the drivers, who were shown more than once for driving under alcohol influence, were again in tax.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the air that has been exhaled and prevents car start when the driver has made an alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is determined that is higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the cost is borne by the person who imposes the penalty.
