Some children speak at night
I mean not those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who speak during sleep.
If it happens to you for the first time, in the best case, you will be scared, but in reality it has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and young people.
Of course, more than one of you has been told that you have spoken at night.
This phenomenon may occur occasionally (once in life, for example during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child cannot remember anything.
There is no reason to cause this phenomenon.
Often, links are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, enuresis noctura (bed wet at night), speaking in sleep, but there is no reason for that.
As we have mentioned earlier, it may be very high fiber, stress or overload.
In any case, this is a little explored phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks quietly in individual words, whispers or it can be quite a opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and to be advised by a specialist in order to check whether there is a problem that causes fear and in this way comes about.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with the sleep apnea or with the stress).
