The Group's internal rules say that in advance no new service will be applied for, but only if it is already available. However, the events of the coming months and years could again be a lot more serious: while some believe that Google's book and magazine or archiving project is now assuming that the company will soon have to deal with the Supreme Court, others are concerned about the "health" system that allows the creation of a complete health profile based on findings, doctors and problems.
And the fact that Google is building a genetic database, the next generation of Sci-Fi authors already supplies the fabric - for example, "Scroogled," the famous novel by Cory Doctorov describes a future in the best Orwelle manier, in which a human being, thanks to Google-related data, becomes terrifying.
